## Remarks  
 <span data-ttu-id="496cf-104">类的读写属性使用特性进行标记 <xref:System.Management.Instrumentation.ManagementConfigurationAttribute> 。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="496cf-104">The read-write properties of a class are marked with the <xref:System.Management.Instrumentation.ManagementConfigurationAttribute> attribute.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="496cf-105">此外，每个读写属性可以是以下两种类型之一： <xref:System.Management.Instrumentation.ManagementConfigurationType.Apply> 或 <xref:System.Management.Instrumentation.ManagementConfigurationType.OnCommit> 。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="496cf-105">In addition, each read-write property can be one of two types: <xref:System.Management.Instrumentation.ManagementConfigurationType.Apply> or <xref:System.Management.Instrumentation.ManagementConfigurationType.OnCommit>.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="496cf-106">如果某个类具有配置为 OnCommit 的读写属性，则该类应具有用 ManagementCommit 特性标记的方法。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="496cf-106">If a class has read-write properties that are configured as OnCommit, the class should have a method that is marked with the ManagementCommit attribute.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="496cf-107">设置所有 OnCommit 属性后，将调用关联的方法。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="496cf-107">The associated method will be called when all OnCommit properties have been set.</span></span>  
  
 <span data-ttu-id="496cf-108">标记的方法不是线程安全的。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="496cf-108">The marked method is not thread safe.</span></span>  
  
 <span data-ttu-id="496cf-109">如果没有使用 ManagementCommit 特性标记的方法，则类会自行管理配置更新，而不会指示更新已完成。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="496cf-109">If no method is marked with the ManagementCommit attribute, the class manages the configuration updates by itself without any indication that the update has completed.</span></span>  
  
 <span data-ttu-id="496cf-110">用 ManagementCommit 特性标记的方法不采用任何参数，并且具有 void 返回类型。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="496cf-110">The method marked with the ManagementCommit attribute does not take any parameters and it has a void return type.</span></span>  
  
   
  
## Examples  
  
```csharp  
public class Process  
{  
    /// Key attribute marks a key property. Keys are not changeable.  
    /// Keys have to be unique information.  
    [ManagementKey]  
    public int Id   
    {  
        get {    }  
    }  
  
    /// ManagementConfiguration stands for read/write manageable  
    /// property from a read/write field.  
    [ManagementConfiguration]  
    public string UserDefinedString;  
  
    [ManagementCommit]  
    void SaveOnDevice();  
}  
```
